column4: C code: int main(){ Integer x; return 0; } Which compiler phase throws an error?
column7: “Integer” is tokenized as an identifier; syntax is valid as a declaration if it were a typedef. The error is that the type name is undeclared → semantic error.

column4: Which of the following is NOT an intermediate representation (IR)?
column7: Symbol table is a data structure, not an IR. TAC/CFG/AST are IRs.

column4: Two-level inclusive caches (L1 write-through) statements: S1) Read misses in write-through L1 don’t write back dirty lines to L2. S2) Write-allocate must be used with write-through and no-write-allocate with write-back. Which is correct?
column5: ["S1 true, S2 true","S1 false, S2 false","S1 true, S2 false","S1 false, S2 true"]
column7: Read miss in WT L1 does not cause L1 writeback. Write-allocate can be used with write-back (and often is); S2 is false.

column4: CRC generator g(x)=x^3+x+1; message m=1100 (m4..m0). What are the 3 CRC bits c2c1c0?

column4: A computer with 4 MHz processor has a DMA controller that transfers 8 bytes in 1 cycle via cycle stealing. If 1% of processor cycles are used for DMA, what is the data transfer rate (in bits/sec)?
column7: Cycle time = 0.25 µs. 1% ⇒ 25 µs interval. In 25 µs, 8 bytes (64 bits) transferred ⇒ (64/25×10⁻⁶) = 2.56×10⁶ bps = 25,60,000.

column4: If two distinct non-zero variables x and y are such that (x+y) is proportional to (x−y), then the value of x/y is
column5: ["Depends on xy","Depends only on x and not on y","Depends only on y and not on x","is a constant"]
column7: (x+y)=k(x−y) ⇒ x(1+k)=y(−1+k) ⇒ x/y=(k−1)/(k+1), a constant (for fixed k).

column4: For positive non-zero p and q, if log(p²+q²)=log p + log q + 2 log 3, then the value of (p⁴+q⁴)/(p²q²) is
column7: From log(p²+q²)=log(pq)+log 9 ⇒ p²+q²=9pq. Then (p⁴+q⁴)/(p²q²)=((p²+q²)²−2p²q²)/(p²q²)=(81−2)=79.

column4: A 2,000 kcal diet has macronutrient percentages as in the pie chart; fats (unsaturated+saturated+trans) total 45%. Given 9 kcal/g for fats, total fat grams consumed is

column4: A 20 cm × 8 cm rectangle is folded 3 times along the line of symmetry perpendicular to its long edge. The final folded sheet perimeter (cm) is
column7: Each fold halves the long side: 20→10→5; short side halves once to 4. Final L×B = 5×4 ⇒ perimeter = 2(5+4)=18 cm.
